<subSubSection id="65B9ACCD1BE72B7744630DF9C39B25D3" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0D0F0588D3FFE8AC689AFBB9E7AC43C0" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1169B4A9ABC79F4F60AFB4E51FBC2B75" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="F149ADD2949A58C1202514EB88AFB28A" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Bankeraceae" genus="Boletopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Boletopsis nothofagi" order="Thelephorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nothofagi">Boletopsis nothofagi</taxonomicName>
differs from described species in the more elongate spores with a narrow central waist, granular extra-cellular material becoming green in KOH and habitat in 
<taxonomicName id="855AAE08C315ECECFC5CDE3902569980" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nothofagus" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Nothofagus</taxonomicName>
forests (
<bibRefCitation id="74F311D628597F3191E85DD40D3002BB" author="Niemala, T" journalOrPublisher="Karstenia" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="12 - 28" title="On Fennoscandian polypores 10. Boletopsis leucomelaena and B. grisea described and llustrated." volume="29" year="1989">Niemala and Saarenoska 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D86C98E098B66BBF7635B7CD8DCEB5F" author="Harrison, K" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte Nova Hedwigia" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="119 - 121" title="A New Species of Boletopsis." volume="51" year="1975">Harrison 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="22121899AA7BFF1A82B2A3691844C2F1" author="Watling, R" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of Scotland" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="81 - 92" title="A new species of Boletopsis associated with Pinus sylvestris L in Scotland." url="10.1080/03746600608685110" volume="58" year="2006">Watling and Milne 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
